reviewText: Hadn't seen this one before. Very good..
A great Concert. Has many of the songs which inspired me on in my faith.The Beginnings Concert

Such a great concert! The DVD/CD combo is excellent...great sound and quality...everyone involved in the making of this did an amazing job. I highly recommend The Beginnings Concert for anyone who listened to CCM music during the 70's and 80's.
If you like the old Jesus Music Artist this is for you! Great and smooth video and the music makes you think you are there

I purchased this DVD more than 2 years ago and forgot to post a review.  First of all, I adored hearing the artists who were recording at the time I was saved.  The most stunning and wonderful event in my life, my salvation experience.  Thank you Jesus.  Needless to say, I enjoyed this DVD very much.  I'd never known Janny Grein previously and I just fell in love with her performance and love for the Lord.  Now, I just find out that she passed away in August 2011.  Sure wish there was much more of her CD's etc to enjoy and worship to now that she's gone.  Bless you Janny!

The Beginnings Concert took me back to the early days of ccm.  Most of these tunes sound just like I remembered them.  "Little Country Church" still rocks.  There are a lot of goose bump moments.  Reba Rambo McGuire brings down the house with "Oohs and "Aahs."  Enjoyed this very much--it brought back great memories.
